---
/**
 * About Page — Layer 1
 * Journey milestones (abstracted, not raw), beliefs, Tamil roots.
 * SPAR rule: abstract the lesson, never expose the event.
 */
import "../styles/global.css";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import TamilRoot from "../components/TamilRoot.astro";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>About | Naveen Riaz</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Naveen Riaz Mohamed Kani. Pattern connector. Career across 10 countries. Building frameworks that treat organisations as living systems."
    />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="About | Naveen Riaz" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Naveen Riaz Mohamed Kani. Pattern connector. Career across 10 countries. Building frameworks that treat organisations as living systems." />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://naveenriaz.com/og-image.png" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://naveenriaz.com/about/" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  </head>
  <body class="section-about">
    <Header activeNav="about" />

    <main class="container container--narrow">
      <section class="page-hero section">
        <h1>
          <p class="page-title">Naveen Riaz Mohamed Kani</p>
          <p class="page-subtitle">நவீன் ரியாஸ் மொஹமத் கனி</p>
        </h1>
      </section>

      <section class="section--tight">
        <p>
          I connect patterns across domains that others treat as separate.
          Organisations, cognition, ancient wisdom, and AI are not four topics
          to me, they are one system viewed from four angles.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="divider"><img src="/logo-h.svg" alt="ஃ" /></div>

      <!-- The Journey: abstracted milestones -->
      <section class="section--tight">
        <h2>The Journey</h2>

        <div class="journey-timeline">
          <div class="journey-milestone">
            <div class="milestone-marker" style="--marker-color: var(--mind-color);"></div>
            <div class="milestone-content">
              <h4>Foundations</h4>
              <p>Born in Nagercoil. Studied Bachelor of Engineering (BE) in Computer Science & Engineering at PSG College of Technology, Coimbatore.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="journey-milestone">
            <div class="milestone-marker" style="--marker-color: var(--body-color);"></div>
            <div class="milestone-content">
              <h4>Career Lens</h4>
              <p>Started working in Cognizant, Chennai. An engineering mind meets an obsession with patterns. The question was never "how does this code work?" but "why do systems behave this way?"</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="journey-milestone">
            <div class="milestone-marker" style="--marker-color: var(--body-color);"></div>
            <div class="milestone-content">
              <h4>Global Lens</h4>
              <p>The career spanned from India to Hong Kong, USA, Malaysia, UK, and now settled in Australia. Each culture added a layer. Each move stripped away assumptions.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="journey-milestone">
            <div class="milestone-marker" style="--marker-color: var(--soul-color);"></div>
            <div class="milestone-content">
              <h4>The Crucible</h4>
              <p>A season that broke the old model. A health wake-up call, the kind that reorders priorities permanently. The body teaches what the mind refuses to learn.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="journey-milestone">
            <div class="milestone-marker" style="--marker-color: var(--body-color);"></div>
            <div class="milestone-content">
              <h4>The Rebuild</h4>
              <p>Coaching a team of 50+ people. Started lectures and training sessions in colleges. Discovering that teaching is the highest form of learning. The introvert who avoided small talk found his voice in structured dialogue.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="journey-milestone">
            <div class="milestone-marker" style="--marker-color: var(--mind-color);"></div>
            <div class="milestone-content">
              <h4>The Purpose</h4>
              <p>Building something that outlasts a career. Every tool, book, and framework on this site is part of that. Not a startup, not a brand, a way of seeing that others can carry forward.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="divider"><img src="/logo-h.svg" alt="ஃ" /></div>

      <section class="section--tight">
        <h2>What I Believe</h2>
        <p>
          Every organisation, community, product, and service is alive. Nurture its Mind, Body & Soul. Watch it
          thrive.
        </p>
        <p>
          Intentional decisions define the quality of outcomes. The quality of your
          deliberation determines the quality of your life.
        </p>
        <p>
          Ancient wisdom is not outdated. It is under-applied. The Thirukkural
          is the most compressed leadership manual I have ever encountered.
        </p>
      </section>

      <TamilRoot
        tamil="அறிவு"
        transliteration="Arivu"
        meaning="Knowledge, wisdom, understanding. The Tamil word carries a weight that 'knowledge' in English does not: it implies both knowing and the responsibility that comes with knowing."
        kural={`எப்பொருள் யார்யார்வாய்க் கேட்பினும் அப்பொருள்\nமெய்ப்பொருள் காண்ப தறிவு.`}
        kuralNumber={423}
        kuralTranslation="True knowledge is discerning the truth in whatever is heard, from whoever speaks it."
      />
    </main>

    <Footer />

  </body>
</html>
